Let me introduce you to my friend Sarah and her husband Ryan. They're one of the most beautiful, giving, selfless, faithful, loving, caring, compassionate, fun, couples I know. They have a big heart and a tremendous desire to have a baby of their own. If you are a parent, then you know the joy kids bring unto your life. For them, that road has been a difficult one. So they've embarked on the road of adoption (you may read more about their story on the link provided) . I am asking that if you or someone you may know is looking into giving up their baby for adoption, that you'd consider them. If you swipe right you'll see all the INFO you'll need to contact them. I will also have their link on my profile until they get match with a mom/baby. If you feel incline to re-post this on your feed or stories please do so. What a blessing it would be if the word gets spread and they find a match! Thank you in advance 💛.

She does well with large size dogs. Chata really into her food, so she needs to be left alone while eating, otherwise she will snap.
Chata had a full Vet check up, she is a pretty healthy dog and her hip, elbow X-rays in great condition.
Chata will be available for an adult home only, no kids. Chata likes her space at the beginning with strangers, so her adopter needs to be patient and gain her trust.

Interested in adopting her? Please fill out an Application on our website at: www.angelsbarkrescue.org #ilovegermanshepherds #germanshepherdofinstagram #germanshepherddog
